cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the behavior of users and a jammer in a communication channel, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) as the users and the jammer are participating in a non-cooperative zero-sum game. The paper also discusses power allocation strategies, which is a topic in networked control systems (cs.NI) and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves optimization (cs.MM) as the objective function is to maximize the mutual information in the channel.
